  GPLv2 or later. This means:
  
  - You may freely distribute the binary
  - You must provide access to corresponding source code
  - You must include a copy of the GPLv2 license text
  - Any modifications to GPLv2 code must be disclosed

SOURCE DISTRIBUTION:
  Individual source files retain their original licenses as indicated in their
  file headers and in this license document. You must respect each license
  when distributing specific files.

